# DaPlex supported-browser floor — the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for the build.
# @angular/build (esbuild) reads this for BOTH JS down-leveling AND CSS autoprefixing.
# Target: iOS 13 Safari (WebKit, span 13.0–13.7) + current Firefox (Gecko, incl. ESR).
#
# Without this file, Angular silently targets ~Safari 18 and emits native ?. / ?? / ??=
# / ES2022 class fields that iOS 13 cannot parse → white screen on load.
#
# Angular WILL print: "Unsupported browsers: ios_saf 13.x, safari 13" — this is EXPECTED
# and benign (Angular disclaims official support but still down-levels JS for them).
# Do NOT treat that warning as a build failure, and do NOT add `dead`/`>0.5%` queries
# (they would subtract iOS 13 back out).
last 2 Chrome versions
last 2 Edge versions
last 2 Firefox versions
Firefox ESR
Safari >= 13
iOS >= 13
